Durban - Three people were seriously injured when an AK47-wielding gunman opened fire on the vehicle that they were travelling in, in Milky Way Road, Shongweni, at the weekend. 
It is believed that four people were travelling back home after attended the funeral of a taxi industry operator in KwaNdengezi when the shooting occurred.

Blue Security spokesperson, Andreas Mathios said the incident took place after 2pm on Sunday afternoon. 
Mathios said an AK47 and a 9mm pistol were used. 
 "The driver, whose vehicle was being shot at, lost control of the vehicle and crashed into the gate of a property in Milky Way Road. The vehicle rolled during the crash. It is believed that at least three people were injured during the shooting," he said. 

Mathios said the wounded were rushed to hospital by their friends who rushed to the scene. 
"It is unclear at this stage whether the suspects had followed the victims' vehicle or whether they had been lying in ambush before opening fire," Mathios said.
Police are investigating further. 

The Mercury